{% block introduction %}
<p>
  This model is an application profile for Data4Wallonia. It allows to express the taxonomy used to classify concepts in Data4Wallonia portal.
</p>
<p>
  D4WTA-AP is designed to meet the following use cases:
  <ul>
    <li>facilitating the findability of the concepts;</li>
    <li>being compliant with existing standards to reach semantic interoperability.</li>
  </ul>
</p>
<p>
  The specification of the Data4Wallonia Taxonomy Application Profile is represented in a UML class diagram.
  The figure here beneath shows the full profile which includes the classes and properties that define the taxonomy itself.
</p>
{% endblock %}


{% block summary %}
<section id="abstract">
    <h2>Abstract</h2>
D4WTA-AP provides a minimal common basis within Data4Wallonia to describe a taxonomy.
</section>
{% endblock %}

